issue.title: Consistent crash with Redis 6.2.4
issue.body:
Redis 6.2.4 crashes consistently when loaded with a release build of the current (90ba30273ce0dcd3e7a91704f7f4900b1e5a8c4a) commit. This happens before the server finishes loading, with the command `redis-server --loadmodule /home/ubuntu/repositories/RedisJSON/target/release/librejson.so --logfile /tmp/redisgMYd0p/redis.log --port 40505 --bind 127.0.0.1`.

Ubuntu 22.0

comment.body: Since v2.6 GA the minimal supported Redis version is 7.2

- #1102 Added support for CBL-Mariner 2
- #1099 Added support for RHEL9 and Rocky Linux 9
